SIMPLE: monsoon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: monsoon
<hw>mon*soon"</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧n*s⟦oomac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Malay <ets>m⟦umac⟧sim</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>mausim</ets> a time,
season: cf. F. <ets>monson</ets>, <ets>mousson</ets>, Sr.
<ets>monzon</ets>, Pg. <ets>mon⟦cced⟧⟦atil⟧o</ets>, It.
<ets>monsone</ets>.]</ety> <def>A wind blowing part of the year from one
direction, alternating with a wind from the opposite direction; -- a
term applied particularly to periodical winds of the Indian Ocean, which
blow from the southwest from the latter part of May to the middle of
September, and from the northeast from about the middle of October to
the middle of December.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A heavy rainfall in India associated with the
southwest monsoon{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The season in which the monsoon{2} occurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monster</ent>⟦br⟧
